@node "par" "Property Auction Rule"

"PROPERTY AUCTION RULE" - The official rules say that if a person doesn't
want to buy the property he lands on it must be auctioned off.  The one who
refused the property will get the last bid.  If no-one else bids the one who
refused it won't get any bid and the property will go back to the Bank.  If
'NO' is selected then properties will NOT be auctioned if the person who 
lands on it doesn't want it.


During an auction the minimum bids are as follows:

American   $1
British    £1
Australian $1
Star Wars  $1
NASCAR     $1

German    Dm2
Swedish   Kr20
French    Fr100
Italian    £100 

Default is 'YES'.
@endnode
@node "lhh" "Limited Houses And Hotels"

"LIMITED HOUSES AND HOTELS" - Each Monopoly set comes with only 32 houses
and 12 hotels.  According to the official rules, once the houses are gone,
no-one may build more houses until more houses are turned into the Bank. 
The same goes for hotels.  This is intended to make it easier to force other
players into bankruptcy.  Clicking 'NO' will give you unlimited houses and
hotels.

Default is 'YES'.
@endnode
@node "scc" "Sell Out Of Jail Cards To Bank"

"SELL OUT OF JAIL CARDS TO BANK" - The official rules have no provision for
selling Get Out Of Jail Free Cards to the bank.  If you click 'YES' you can
get half what it cost to get out of Jail ($25 in the USA version) from a Get
Out Of Jail Free card from the 'Sell' menu.  If you click 'NO' you can still
sell them to other players for any amount you can get.

Default is 'NO'.
@endnode
@node "fpj" "Free Parking Jackpot"

"FREE PARKING JACKPOT" - The official rules have nothing special for Free
Parking but many people like a jackpot.  Clicking 'YES' will cause money
from Luxury Tax, Income Tax, Chance and Community Chest to be given to the
next person who lands on Free Parking.

Default is 'NO'.
@endnode
@node "pmr" "Playmaster Rules"

"PLAYMASTER RULES" -Selecting 'YES' will add three things:

1) Random auctions of unowned property every 4-6 turns.

2) Buybacks.  After all properties are owned the computer will buyback
singly owned properties of one random color group every 4-6 turns.  The
owners will get the face value of the properties unless they are mortgaged
in which case they will get 1/2 the face value.  The properties will then be
auctioned off one at a time.

3) Loans.  If a player owns all the properties of a color group and none of
them are mortgaged, he may take a loan out on them.  The player will get the
full face value of the properties.  The player must pay back the loan amount
plus 10% sometime after 7 turns.  The player may not pay the loan back early
or late.  Once a property has had a loan on it, it cannot be mortgaged for
the rest of the game - even if the property is sold to another player.  If a
property is sold the new owner is responsible for the loan.

In case you are interested, The Monopoly Playmaster was an electronic device
made by Parker Brothers that was designed to be used in conjunction with a
Monopoly board in order to make the game play faster.  The Playmaster
controlled dice rolls, turns, auctions, buybacks, loans and more. 

Default is 'NO'.
@endnode
@node "qdr" "Quick Dice Rolls"

"QUICK DICE ROLLS" - By default the dice flash some different values to
simulate actual dice rolling.  Selecting 'YES' will just show the single
values.

Default is 'NO'.
@endnode
@node "qst" "Quick Start"

"QUICK START" - Selecting 'YES' will cause 3 things to happen

1)  Each player will get 2 randomly selected properties and pay the normal
    price for them

2)  You only have to buy 3 houses in order to buy a hotel.  The rent for a
    hotel stays the same.

3)  The game ends after the second bankruptcy.  Of course this only has an
    effect if there are 4 players.

Default is 'NO'
@endnode
@node "fpl" "Fast Play"

"FAST PLAY" - Selecting 'YES' will remove most of the delays from the game
increasing playing speed.

Default is 'NO'

@endnode
@node "btb" "Bankrupt Props To Bank"

"BANKRUPT PROPS TO BANK" - Selecting 'YES' will give all properties owned
by a player who quits or goes bankrupt back to the bank.  The next person
who lands on the properties may buy them as if they had never been owned.

Selecting 'NO' means that when a player quits or goes bankrupt, all his
properties will be auctioned off one at a time

Default is 'NO'

@endnode
@node "oin" "Ownership Indicators"

"OWNERSHIP INDICATORS" - Selecting 'YES' will put a small bar next to each
property showing who owns it.  The color of the bar will match the player's
color.

Default is 'NO'

@endnode
@node "hmp" "Players"

Clicking on the player buttons lets you select the number and type of
players.  The button cycles between "Human", "Amiga", "Expert", and "off"

Human  - Human controls the player.
Amiga  - Computer controls the player.
Expert - Computer controls the player, but is harder to beat.
off    - no player.

Any combination may be used, but there must be at least 2 players.

Default is 4 human players.
@endnode
