@node "int" "International Version"

As you may have noticed, this is an International version.  In addition to
the standard American version, there are also British, Australian, French,
Italian, German, Swedish, Star Wars and NASCAR versions.

The main difference between them are the property names and the property
values.

In the USA, UK, AUS, STARWARS and NASCAR versions you get 200 for passing
"Go".  The FRA and ITA versions are 100 X this (i.e. you get 20000 for
passing "Go").  The German version is 2 X the USA version (400 at "Go") and
the Swedish version is 20 X (4000 at "Go").  All the property values, taxes,
rent, etc increase accordingly.  In other words, the most expensive property
cost the same money you would get by passing "Go" twice, no matter which
version you are playing.

The American, Australian, Star Wars and NASCAR version give you a choice of
paying 200 or 10% of your assets at the first tax (4 spaces after Go).  In
the other versions you must pay what you would get at "Go".

In the American, Star Wars and NASCAR versions the tax near the end of the
board (2 spaces before "Go") is 75.  In the other versions it's 1/2 of what
you'd get at "Go".

